WEBVTT

00:03.135 --> 00:03.976
[ Sighs ]

00:04.214 --> 00:05.714
I love springtime,

00:05.749 --> 00:07.916
when the bulky sweatshirts
come off,

00:07.951 --> 00:11.119
and you can see which guys
were in the gym all winter.

00:11.154 --> 00:13.455
What's that, snot?
Why am I so distracted today?

00:15.359 --> 00:18.126
'Cause I'm craving something,
something I've never had.

00:18.161 --> 00:19.761
Potato boobs!

00:19.796 --> 00:21.229
[ Chomping ]

00:21.265 --> 00:23.798
You can have
the starchy simulacra.

00:23.800 --> 00:27.352
I need to -- nay, I <i> will</i> touch
the real thing.

00:27.472 --> 00:30.821
_

00:30.941 --> 00:34.609
Exactly! What kind of guys
get boob at this school?

00:34.645 --> 00:37.212
I could be Tanya Johnson's baby.

00:37.247 --> 00:40.749
[ Speaks inaudibly ]
[ Coos ]

00:40.784 --> 00:43.718
But he's doing that. Or...

00:43.754 --> 00:45.570
[ Indistinct conversations ]

00:45.622 --> 00:47.455
<i>Hello.</i>

00:47.491 --> 00:49.424
Varsity athletes touch boob!

00:49.459 --> 00:51.693
'Cause they got
those cool letter jackets!

00:51.728 --> 00:54.963
[ Scoffs ] And how are you gonna
become a varsity athlete?

00:55.083 --> 00:58.005
_

00:58.869 --> 01:00.869
Hardly anyone's going out
for water polo.

01:00.904 --> 01:03.271
I-it's like they're
giving letter jackets away!

01:03.307 --> 01:05.507
Or you could buy
a foreign knockoff jacket

01:05.542 --> 01:06.875
and say you transferred in.

01:06.910 --> 01:10.612
I really think people don't
remember us.

01:11.214 --> 01:13.598
♪

01:13.650 --> 01:16.484
♪ Good morning, U.S.A.

01:16.520 --> 01:19.904
♪ I got a feelin' that
it's gonna be a wonderful day ♪

01:19.940 --> 01:23.191
♪ the sun in the sky
has a smile on his face ♪

01:23.243 --> 01:27.495
♪ and he's shinin' a salute
to the American race ♪

01:29.533 --> 01:32.534
♪ oh, boy, it's swell to say

01:32.536 --> 01:35.203
♪ good --
♪ good morning, U.S.A.

01:35.205 --> 01:43.364
<font color="#ec14bd">Sync & corrections by honeybunny
www.addic7ed.com</font>

01:43.680 --> 01:46.631
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:46.683 --> 01:48.967
Man, these C.I.A. auctions
are amazing.

01:49.019 --> 01:50.969
There's so much cool stuff.

01:51.021 --> 01:52.520
Hey, can we get
a Farsi translator?

01:52.556 --> 01:53.855
Please, please, please?

01:53.890 --> 01:55.607
Will you feed her
and take her for walks?

01:55.642 --> 01:57.359
No.

01:57.394 --> 01:58.693
And sold!

01:58.729 --> 02:00.528
This working hellfire missile

02:00.564 --> 02:03.898
goes to the man stroking a cat
menacingly in the front row.

02:03.934 --> 02:05.483
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, it's not for me.

02:05.535 --> 02:07.736
It's for downtown Pittsburgh.

02:07.788 --> 02:09.738
[ Cat purrs ]

02:09.789 --> 02:13.241
Our next item is
a 26-foot sailboat

02:13.243 --> 02:16.378
seized off the coast
of <i> Colombia.</i>

02:16.413 --> 02:17.746
Wow.
Wow.

02:17.781 --> 02:19.948
I've always wanted to be
a boat guy.

02:19.983 --> 02:22.283
I know, right?
Hanging out on the deck,

02:22.319 --> 02:24.419
washing down fries
from the marina café

02:24.454 --> 02:25.920
with some cheap canned beer,

02:25.956 --> 02:27.856
making constant small repairs,

02:27.891 --> 02:29.391
getting sunburned

02:29.426 --> 02:31.025
and complaining
the whole time...

02:31.061 --> 02:32.727
Sounds like heaven.

02:32.763 --> 02:35.563
Why don't we start the bidding
at $5,000?

02:35.599 --> 02:37.699
Right here!
I see $5,000. Do I have --

02:37.734 --> 02:39.033
$10,000!
$20,000!

02:39.069 --> 02:40.568
$50,000!

02:40.604 --> 02:41.803
What the hell is going on?!

02:41.838 --> 02:43.405
'Scusies?

02:43.440 --> 02:46.024
Has the Colombian boat
been searched for cocaine?

02:46.076 --> 02:48.676
Uh, yes. There is no cocaine
on the boat.

02:48.712 --> 02:49.978
Take backs.
Me, too.

02:50.013 --> 02:51.413
I'm out.

02:51.448 --> 02:53.515
Sold to the transvestite
in the red dress.

02:53.550 --> 02:55.517
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

02:55.552 --> 02:56.918
He is good.

02:56.953 --> 02:59.754
He's got a better eye
than Garry Marshall.

03:02.717 --> 03:04.250
Good afternoon, men,

03:04.285 --> 03:06.671
and welcome to
water polo tryouts.

03:06.791 --> 03:08.921
I'm the new coach,
James Hetfield.

03:08.956 --> 03:10.523
I know what you're thinking.

03:10.558 --> 03:13.125
"Whoa, the James Hetfield
from Metallica?"

03:13.160 --> 03:15.027
The answer is no way...

03:15.062 --> 03:17.162
even though
I look and sound like him

03:17.198 --> 03:18.697
and have all his guitars.

03:18.733 --> 03:19.999
The point is, if I had to deal

03:20.034 --> 03:22.034
with the kind of pressure
that guy's under,

03:22.069 --> 03:23.669
I'd probably crack

03:23.704 --> 03:25.638
and end up as
a high school water polo coach.

03:25.673 --> 03:27.706
So, it's a good thing
that I'm just

03:27.742 --> 03:29.775
this very different
James Hetfield.

03:31.679 --> 03:33.879
Okay, I appreciate
everyone's interest in the team,

03:33.915 --> 03:37.316
but I can only keep 13 boys.

03:37.351 --> 03:40.119
And...there are 13 of you
trying out.

03:40.154 --> 03:41.320
Okay, we're good.

03:41.355 --> 03:43.155
Sweet!
[ Door bangs open ]

03:43.190 --> 03:44.790
Not so...

03:44.825 --> 03:46.091
Uhh!

03:46.127 --> 03:47.693
[ Groans ] Not...

03:47.728 --> 03:49.862
not so fast!

03:49.897 --> 03:52.781
I'll take <i> my</i> jacket
in a women's medium.

03:52.817 --> 03:54.567
[ Water splashing ]

03:54.619 --> 03:57.069
I got cut
from water polo tryouts!

03:57.071 --> 03:58.571
So you're not on a team,

03:58.573 --> 04:00.155
and I don't get to hang
with the cool parents

04:00.207 --> 04:02.625
for yet another year.
Gotcha.

04:02.660 --> 04:05.311
[ Spoon clatters ]

04:05.346 --> 04:07.346
Great. No one cares.
I care.

04:07.381 --> 04:09.281
Klaus? Wh-where are you?

04:09.317 --> 04:10.783
On the table,

04:10.818 --> 04:13.319
under a pair
of Stan's workout shorts.

04:13.354 --> 04:15.304
He missed
the dirty clothes hamper...

04:15.339 --> 04:17.589
by, like, 80 feet.

04:17.591 --> 04:19.591
So tell me about
this water polo tryout.

04:19.644 --> 04:21.060
How was your eggbeater?

04:21.095 --> 04:23.062
Were your dry passes not to
the strong side hand?

04:23.097 --> 04:24.813
Uh...I don't know.

04:24.849 --> 04:27.266
Wha-- how do <i> you</i> know so much
about water polo?

04:27.268 --> 04:28.817
Eh, growing up,

04:28.853 --> 04:30.603
it was a terrific way
to avoid Turkish people.

04:30.605 --> 04:32.271
Now I can give you
some pointers,

04:32.273 --> 04:34.773
and we will force the coach
to reconsider you.

04:34.825 --> 04:36.075
Awesome!

04:36.110 --> 04:37.693
I am going to make you

04:37.745 --> 04:41.113
the greatest water polo player
in the world!

04:41.165 --> 04:44.333
Yeah!
Step aside, Peter Nordquis!

04:44.368 --> 04:47.252
Wow. You really know
your water polo.

04:47.288 --> 04:48.787
I was just making a name up.

04:48.839 --> 04:51.624
Welp, you got it right.

04:51.676 --> 04:53.726
Ready?
Ready!

04:56.347 --> 04:58.631
There seems to have been
a misunderstanding

04:58.666 --> 05:00.899
about what kind of boat guys
we're gonna be.

05:00.935 --> 05:03.035
Whoa! Is it true you guys
bought a sailboat?!

05:03.070 --> 05:04.703
What do you care?

05:04.739 --> 05:07.039
I love sailing. I practically
grew up on boats.

05:07.074 --> 05:08.340
I taught at sailing camp.

05:08.376 --> 05:10.209
It's the one thing
I'm really good at.

05:10.244 --> 05:12.277
I guess, statistically,
there had to be one.

05:12.313 --> 05:14.013
If you ever need any help
with the boat --

05:14.048 --> 05:15.280
No.
I'd be happy to --

05:15.316 --> 05:16.749
[ cocks gun ]

05:18.052 --> 05:19.652
Guns are a great tool

05:19.687 --> 05:22.021
for keeping things from
escalating out of control.

05:22.056 --> 05:23.956
Now then, about this outfit
disagreement...

05:23.991 --> 05:26.659
[ Cocks gun ]
You're gonna dress my way.

05:26.694 --> 05:28.927
<i>Nice</i> and easy.

05:28.963 --> 05:30.663
See? This works!
No talking!

05:30.715 --> 05:32.414
Let's hit the marina.

05:32.466 --> 05:34.833
[ Panting ]
I just got mugged!

05:34.835 --> 05:37.836
[ Both whistling ]

05:43.060 --> 05:45.978
Ugh. Look at your upper body
bobbing and swaying.

05:46.013 --> 05:48.013
You look like
a broken Barbie doll

05:48.015 --> 05:49.932
surfacing after a ferry sinking.

05:49.984 --> 05:51.850
Well, h-how do I stay still?

05:51.902 --> 05:54.687
Tuck your hips in.
[ Grunts ] Like this?

05:54.739 --> 05:57.189
Ugh. Here, watch me.

05:58.325 --> 06:00.442
Like this.

06:01.779 --> 06:03.078
Dude, what is wrong with you?

06:03.114 --> 06:05.030
I don't understand
what I'm supposed to do!

06:05.082 --> 06:07.499
You're supposed to do this.

06:08.869 --> 06:10.169
Aah!

06:10.204 --> 06:12.004
Tuck...your...hips!

06:12.039 --> 06:13.956
Ooh!

06:14.008 --> 06:17.926
Then you pick up a ball,
eggbeater for elevation,

06:17.962 --> 06:20.053
and fire it into the back of the net.
[ Grunts ]

06:21.382 --> 06:22.881
Whoa.

06:22.883 --> 06:24.349
Holy crap.

06:24.385 --> 06:26.101
You "ratatouille"'d me!

06:26.137 --> 06:27.936
But it's not like
I can go to tryouts with a --

06:27.972 --> 06:30.055
with a -- with a fish
hanging on my shorts.

06:30.057 --> 06:31.974
I'm just gonna
have to keep practicing

06:32.026 --> 06:33.225
till I can do it myself.

06:33.227 --> 06:35.394
[ Scoffs ]
A fish hanging on my shorts.

06:35.396 --> 06:37.980
You know, in Japan,
a fish on your shorts

06:38.032 --> 06:40.733
is eight years of
neither good nor bad luck.

06:40.735 --> 06:43.902
The Japanese
are <i>very</i> superstitious.

06:43.954 --> 06:46.955
[ Metallica's
"Master of Puppets" playing ]

06:50.995 --> 06:54.830
[ Chuckles ] Wow.
Smith, you just made the team.

06:54.882 --> 06:56.081
♪ Master!

06:56.133 --> 06:57.416
♪ Master!
[ Crank clicking ]

06:57.418 --> 07:00.302
♪ Master!

07:00.337 --> 07:03.255
I don't know what got into you,
but I love it.

07:03.257 --> 07:05.140
You're stronger, more confident.

07:05.176 --> 07:08.251
Even your package looks bigger.
Well done.

07:13.234 --> 07:16.802
Nothing wrong with
a fish hanging <i> in</i> your shorts.

07:16.837 --> 07:21.023
[ Both laughing maniacally ]

07:21.075 --> 07:23.104
There's probably a few things
wrong with it.

07:31.955 --> 07:34.122
Look at those guys
with their tit-eating grins.

07:34.174 --> 07:35.790
Time to join 'em.

07:35.792 --> 07:38.293
All right, Klaus.
Take the curly reins.

07:39.379 --> 07:40.846
[ High-pitched voice ] Aah!

07:40.881 --> 07:42.297
Let's go, Scottie!

07:42.349 --> 07:43.832
Focus, Matt!

07:43.867 --> 07:45.183
Please note that I'm here, Nick!

07:45.219 --> 07:46.968
I have to go back to work soon!

07:50.807 --> 07:52.140
[ Whistle blows ]

07:52.192 --> 07:53.859
[ "Master of Puppets" playing ]

07:53.894 --> 07:55.393
[ Spectators cheer ]

07:55.445 --> 07:57.979
♪

07:57.981 --> 07:59.314
[ Spectators cheer ]

08:03.120 --> 08:04.703
[ Spectators cheer ]

08:11.128 --> 08:12.994
[ Spectators cheer ]

08:13.046 --> 08:15.330
♪

08:15.382 --> 08:17.382
Wow! Uh...go, Steve!

08:17.417 --> 08:19.100
Woman: You're Steve's mom?

08:19.136 --> 08:21.336
[ Hesitantly ] Yes?
Your son's a superstar!

08:21.371 --> 08:22.971
What are you doing
way over there?

08:23.006 --> 08:24.906
You <i> have</i> to sit with us!

08:24.942 --> 08:27.209
Really?
With the cool parents?

08:27.244 --> 08:30.345
Let me just check for something
in my purse.

08:30.347 --> 08:32.898
Yes! Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes!

08:32.933 --> 08:34.683
[Bleep] Yes!

08:34.735 --> 08:36.183
♪ Master!

08:36.236 --> 08:37.852
♪ Master!
[ Spectators cheering ]

08:39.273 --> 08:41.856
Great first game, men.
That was as exciting

08:41.909 --> 08:43.991
as singing in front
of 70,000 people

08:44.027 --> 08:46.695
at Giants Stadium...
I would imagine.

08:46.697 --> 08:48.697
Tell you what.
You keep the wins going,

08:48.749 --> 08:50.415
I'm taking you all
to raging waters,

08:50.450 --> 08:52.250
and everyone can bring a friend.

08:52.286 --> 08:53.868
[ All cheer ]

08:53.921 --> 08:56.288
I'm bringing David!

09:00.427 --> 09:01.876
You hear that, buddy?

09:01.878 --> 09:03.178
Raging waters.

09:03.213 --> 09:06.765
So much water, so much rage.

09:06.800 --> 09:08.183
It sounds lovely.

09:08.218 --> 09:10.185
Well, you're gonna be
my plus-one.

09:10.220 --> 09:12.887
Really?
Of course. You're my partner.

09:12.923 --> 09:14.256
Hell, right now

09:14.291 --> 09:17.292
you're my best friend
in the whole world.

09:17.327 --> 09:18.860
[ Breathing unevenly ]

09:18.895 --> 09:21.763
[ Sobbing quietly ]

09:21.798 --> 09:24.032
[ Fizzles ]

09:24.067 --> 09:26.034
[ Water lapping,
seabird calling ]

09:26.069 --> 09:28.403
[ Slurping, gulping ]

09:30.123 --> 09:33.408
Slow down!
No wake!

09:33.460 --> 09:34.909
Assholes.

09:34.911 --> 09:38.797
[ Both gulping ]

09:38.832 --> 09:41.216
Thanks, buddy. [ Slurps ]

09:41.251 --> 09:43.952
Hey, you think we should, uh,
sand something?

09:43.987 --> 09:46.021
Something always needs sanding.

09:46.056 --> 09:47.355
[ Scratching ]

09:47.391 --> 09:48.757
[ Slurps ]

09:48.809 --> 09:50.091
Whew! Hot work.

09:50.093 --> 09:52.010
I could use
another cold one, Stan.

09:52.062 --> 09:53.762
Oh, I think we're out.

09:53.814 --> 09:56.364
Who the...What the...

09:56.400 --> 09:59.000
<i>[ Angelic music plays ]</i>
You boys looked dry.

10:00.404 --> 10:02.237
[ Fizzes ]
Welcome to the marina.

10:02.272 --> 10:04.306
Or as they say in Spanish,

10:04.341 --> 10:06.875
<i>bienvenidos</i> to the marina.

10:06.910 --> 10:08.443
I'm Van Dusen.

10:08.478 --> 10:10.145
I'm Roger, and this is Stan.

10:10.180 --> 10:11.813
We're just up
from the B.V.I.

10:11.848 --> 10:13.448
Ahh. Good sail.

10:13.483 --> 10:15.283
[ Slurps ] Good sail.
[ Slurps ] Good sail. Good sail.

10:15.335 --> 10:18.003
You, uh...painting
after you sand?

10:18.038 --> 10:20.088
You know it.
Ain't that just how it goes?

10:20.123 --> 10:21.373
It surely is.

10:21.425 --> 10:23.008
You know what I tell my friends

10:23.043 --> 10:25.043
when they ask what it's like
to own a boat?

10:25.095 --> 10:28.797
I say,
"Stand under a cold shower

10:28.799 --> 10:31.466
and tear up $100 bills."

10:31.468 --> 10:33.935
[ Laughing ] Oh, my God,
you're perfect!

10:33.970 --> 10:35.970
That's such a perfect thing
to say!

10:36.023 --> 10:38.189
[ Chuckles ] It surely is.

10:38.225 --> 10:42.243
Well, I'll see ya, boys.
I got a fuel line to patch.

10:43.580 --> 10:46.147
Did you see all the melanomas
on his arms?

10:46.183 --> 10:47.449
<i>That's</i> a boat guy.

10:47.484 --> 10:49.384
And now we are, too.
[ Clink ]

10:49.419 --> 10:51.986
How's the sanding going?
I think I've been sanding a window.

10:52.039 --> 10:53.321
Cool.

10:55.992 --> 10:57.292
Morning, mom.

10:57.327 --> 10:59.327
Sit, Steve.
I made you breakfast.

10:59.329 --> 11:01.463
I-I'm kind of running late
for school.

11:01.498 --> 11:03.331
This is just
a little thank-you

11:03.383 --> 11:06.084
for turning me into
one of the cool jock parents.

11:06.136 --> 11:07.502
Well, I'm glad to help.

11:07.554 --> 11:10.338
I never thought I'd be
part of their world

11:10.390 --> 11:14.008
because you and Hayley have
always sucked at everything.

11:14.061 --> 11:17.062
Hey. What's for breakfast?
Nothin'. Beat it.

11:18.348 --> 11:19.898
[ Metallica's
"All Nightmare Long" playing ]

11:19.933 --> 11:22.484
♪ 'Cause we hunt you down
without mercy ♪

11:22.519 --> 11:26.054
♪ hunt you down
all nightmare long ♪

11:26.089 --> 11:28.590
♪ feel us breathe
upon your face ♪

11:28.625 --> 11:31.226
♪ feel us shift,
every move we trace ♪

11:31.261 --> 11:34.062
♪ hunt you down without mercy

11:34.097 --> 11:35.997
♪ hunt you down all night--

11:36.032 --> 11:37.399
[ camera shutter clicks ]

11:37.434 --> 11:39.033
Hey! No cameras!

11:39.035 --> 11:41.035
Are you reaching for something?

11:41.071 --> 11:42.420
Only greatness.

11:42.456 --> 11:43.922
I'm Amy Reed,

11:43.957 --> 11:45.206
sports editor of
the <i> Pearl Bailey Gazette.</i>

11:45.208 --> 11:47.208
A girl trying to make it
in a boys' world.

11:47.210 --> 11:48.960
I respect the hell out of that.

11:49.012 --> 11:50.628
You're taking the school
by storm,

11:50.680 --> 11:53.014
and I want to know
what makes you so good.

11:53.049 --> 11:55.316
My laser-like focus.

11:55.352 --> 11:57.252
[ Breathily ] Oh, my.

11:57.287 --> 11:59.521
To be continued.

12:00.323 --> 12:04.058
Okay, the new name for
your shorts is "The Bone Yard,"

12:04.094 --> 12:06.428
'cause there were
<i>so</i> many bones in there.

12:06.463 --> 12:07.962
Wait, did -- did you also
have a --

12:07.998 --> 12:10.665
Oh, don't tell me you didn't
feel mine, bro.

12:10.700 --> 12:12.267
That's bullshit, man.

12:16.506 --> 12:19.207
Ugh. Soggy.

12:19.242 --> 12:21.209
I can't get a single fry
in my mouth!

12:21.244 --> 12:22.460
[ Thud ]
Aah!

12:22.496 --> 12:24.245
I didn't ask for a beer!

12:24.297 --> 12:26.414
Throwing beers is the only thing
that breaks up the monotony.

12:26.466 --> 12:29.167
Owning a boat sucks.
It does.

12:29.219 --> 12:31.002
It's just constant maintenance.

12:31.054 --> 12:33.972
Should we...I don't know,
try sailing it?

12:34.007 --> 12:37.142
Where? Where in the ocean
do you need to go?

12:37.177 --> 12:40.645
Uh, here's the bill
for this month's slip fee.

12:42.265 --> 12:44.399
Are you kidding me?
Oh, my God!

12:44.434 --> 12:47.519
$14?! That's an hour
of kiln time!

12:47.571 --> 12:49.437
That's it.
We're sellin' the boat.

12:49.439 --> 12:50.688
Heh, good luck.

12:50.740 --> 12:54.159
I've been trying to sell mine
for 15 years.

12:54.194 --> 12:58.246
Trouble is, most people know
how stupid it is to own a boat.

12:58.281 --> 13:00.615
Sometimes I just wish
this thing would sink

13:00.667 --> 13:02.700
so I could get
the insurance money.

13:02.752 --> 13:05.253
That gives me an idea.

13:05.288 --> 13:06.688
Me, too.

13:06.723 --> 13:09.207
Oh, I love it when we have
ideas at the same time!

13:09.259 --> 13:11.709
So do I! Bring it in.

13:11.761 --> 13:13.595
[ Lowered voice ] I think
we should get pinkberry.

13:13.630 --> 13:15.213
[ Lowered voice ] Oh, yum, yum,
yum, yum, yum, yum, yum.

13:15.265 --> 13:18.132
And after that, let's commit...
[ Whispers ] insurance fraud.

13:18.168 --> 13:21.436
[ Whispers ] It's so easy
to make plans with you.

13:24.107 --> 13:25.573
Hey, Klaus.

13:25.609 --> 13:28.276
I see Amy's water polo story
came out in the school paper.

13:28.311 --> 13:31.346
Yeah, pretty cool.
She calls me the "Pool Shark."

13:31.381 --> 13:35.149
"When asked how he got so good
at water polo, Smith replied,

13:35.185 --> 13:38.353
"'by being totally awesome
all by myself with no help.

13:38.388 --> 13:39.654
#blessed'"

13:39.689 --> 13:41.456
what is this crap?!

13:41.491 --> 13:44.158
Come on! I couldn't say
I had a fish in my shorts.

13:44.160 --> 13:45.727
I-I'd get kicked off
the team!

13:45.762 --> 13:47.595
You wouldn't even <i>be</i> on the team

13:47.631 --> 13:49.664
if <i> I</i> wasn't steering you
by the pubes.

13:49.666 --> 13:52.000
Ugh, Klaus, stop being
such a baby.

13:52.052 --> 13:53.384
It's one stupid article.

13:53.420 --> 13:55.169
Yeah, but --
But nothing!

13:55.171 --> 13:57.589
I'm not forgetting about you,
I swear to God!

13:57.641 --> 14:00.174
[ Horn honks ]
Oh, that's the bus to raging waters.

14:00.176 --> 14:02.343
Great, I'll get my stuff.

14:02.345 --> 14:03.561
I'm ready.

14:03.597 --> 14:05.013
<i>Oh.</i> Yeah...

14:05.065 --> 14:06.347
Ugh.

14:06.383 --> 14:08.249
Um, about that...

14:08.285 --> 14:12.186
Come on, Steve!
Thanks for inviting me!

14:12.222 --> 14:13.788
Dude.

14:13.823 --> 14:17.775
I know I invited you first,
but you can't compete with that.

14:19.613 --> 14:24.032
If it's competition you want,
then prepare to lose.

14:24.084 --> 14:25.416
Uh, but not right now,
of course,

14:25.452 --> 14:26.784
because you're killing it.

14:26.836 --> 14:28.703
You're taking a hot girl
to a water park,

14:28.755 --> 14:33.091
and I'm stuck home in a bowl.
<i>But</i> things can change.

14:33.126 --> 14:37.512
Oh, yes, change is in the air.

14:37.547 --> 14:40.597
Change is a-comin'.

14:40.717 --> 14:42.590
Chan--

14:45.011 --> 14:47.078
It's been a hell of a season,
men.

14:47.113 --> 14:49.513
You've played for me,
for each other,

14:49.549 --> 14:50.965
and for this letter jacket.

14:51.000 --> 14:54.001
Now let's go send
Fairfax Country Day School...

14:54.053 --> 14:58.089
♪ Off to never-never land, ah!

15:04.931 --> 15:07.565
'Sup?
Ready to do this?

15:07.600 --> 15:08.933
I'm thinking today

15:08.935 --> 15:11.769
the pool shark will be
doing it by himself.

15:11.771 --> 15:14.605
I'm too engrossed
in this week's cafeteria menu.

15:14.607 --> 15:16.607
[ Sighs ] Is this about
raging waters?

15:16.659 --> 15:17.942
Sloppy Joe Friday.

15:17.994 --> 15:20.611
Start your weekend
on the toilet.

15:20.663 --> 15:23.114
Fine. I don't need you.
Yeah, yeah.

15:23.116 --> 15:25.082
This is gonna be like
the part of "Ratatouille"

15:25.118 --> 15:26.617
when the human realizes

15:26.619 --> 15:28.002
he doesn't need the rat
any more,

15:28.037 --> 15:30.004
and then he's really successful
on his own,

15:30.039 --> 15:31.706
and then the movie ends.

15:33.126 --> 15:34.625
The movie doesn't end

15:34.677 --> 15:37.628
when you fall asleep
with your blankie, Steve.

15:37.664 --> 15:38.896
[ Whistle blows ]

15:38.931 --> 15:40.164
[ Cheering ]

15:40.199 --> 15:42.133
[ Grunting ]

15:42.135 --> 15:43.517
[ Coughs ]

15:43.553 --> 15:46.053
[ Smack ]

15:46.105 --> 15:48.472
The hell's wrong with you,
Smith?!

15:48.474 --> 15:49.940
Is Steve all right?

15:49.976 --> 15:53.477
I don't think so.
He's losing his mother's love.

15:53.479 --> 15:55.980
[ Grunting ]

15:56.032 --> 15:58.816
Look at you, quivering like
the Italian army.

15:58.818 --> 16:01.652
That's because your legs are as
weak as the Italian air force,

16:01.704 --> 16:04.538
which is why you've taken fewer
shots than the Italian Navy.

16:04.574 --> 16:06.040
I'm not just gonna float here

16:06.075 --> 16:08.793
and let you compare me to
the entire Italian armed forces.

16:08.828 --> 16:12.129
Well, what are you gonna
do about it, paisan?

16:12.165 --> 16:14.048
I'm gonna use all my strength

16:14.083 --> 16:16.500
to be the pool shark
I know I can be!

16:16.502 --> 16:20.755
[ Triumphant music playing ]

16:26.512 --> 16:28.179
[ Glass shatters ]

16:28.181 --> 16:30.181
Oh! Just missed.

16:30.233 --> 16:34.685
[ Weakly ] And I used...
all my strength.

16:36.022 --> 16:37.855
[ Thinking ] <i>Oh, God.</i>

16:37.857 --> 16:40.191
<i>Am I drowning?</i>

16:40.243 --> 16:42.576
<i>I</i> am <i>drowning.</i>

16:42.612 --> 16:44.829
<i>My life is flashing</i>
<i>before my eyes.</i>

16:44.864 --> 16:47.698
[ Claps hands ]
[ Singsongy ] Come to mama!

16:49.202 --> 16:50.868
[ Thud ]

16:53.840 --> 16:55.539
What?! No!

16:55.591 --> 16:57.925
Have fun tonight, honey.

16:57.960 --> 17:00.761
Give him <i>everything</i> he wants.

17:00.797 --> 17:02.930
You bet.

17:05.134 --> 17:06.934
[ Both moaning ]

17:06.969 --> 17:09.185
No! Those are <i>my</i> boobs!

17:09.222 --> 17:12.056
Stop...ignoring me.

