17:31.711 --> 17:33.994
[ Bubbling ]

17:36.249 --> 17:39.633
[ Coughing, sputtering ]

17:39.669 --> 17:41.886
You okay?
[ Coughs ]

17:41.921 --> 17:45.723
Yeah.
Yeah, I'm better than okay.

17:45.758 --> 17:49.927
It took me being underwater
to finally see things clearly.

17:49.929 --> 17:52.596
That's a great lyric.

17:52.598 --> 17:54.181
I got my confidence back.

17:54.233 --> 17:55.683
I quit.

17:58.871 --> 18:00.638
I have a confession to make.

18:00.673 --> 18:04.241
I didn't become a great
water polo player all by myself.

18:04.277 --> 18:07.812
In fact, the guy that
made me great is here today.

18:07.847 --> 18:09.613
[ Lowered voice ] Dude,
what are you doing?

18:09.649 --> 18:13.217
You see, sometimes one member of
the team gets the spotlight,

18:13.252 --> 18:14.885
even though
he couldn't have done it

18:14.921 --> 18:17.621
without another member --
an important member.

18:17.657 --> 18:20.658
I'm talking about the little guy
in my swimsuit.

18:20.693 --> 18:23.260
And I think it's time
for everybody to meet him.

18:23.296 --> 18:25.679
[ All gasp ]

18:26.883 --> 18:29.383
Welp, it was a good run.

18:29.435 --> 18:31.719
Stop! You'll lose everything.

18:31.771 --> 18:34.021
This guy doesn't get
the attention he deserves.

18:34.056 --> 18:36.807
Maybe 'cause he's so small.
Prove it!

18:36.809 --> 18:40.110
'Scuse me. Sorry.
Just making my way out.

18:40.146 --> 18:41.812
I know how this ends.

18:41.814 --> 18:43.364
He gets a little shy.

18:43.399 --> 18:46.400
M-maybe if I stroke him a bit,
he'll pop his head out.

18:46.452 --> 18:48.152
That's so gross.

18:48.154 --> 18:50.321
I'm so cold.

18:50.323 --> 18:51.956
Are you a varsity athlete?

18:51.991 --> 18:53.991
No. My dad owns
a jacket company.

18:54.043 --> 18:56.710
Oh, my God. [ Giggles ]

18:56.746 --> 18:58.963
Okay, everybody,
I see how this looks.

18:58.998 --> 19:01.832
I'm not a weirdo.
I just have a fish in my shorts.

19:01.884 --> 19:03.834
He's been helping me
get a jacket.

19:03.886 --> 19:06.253
Seemed like a good way
to get to second base.

19:06.305 --> 19:08.923
Thinking about
switching schools.

19:11.394 --> 19:13.677
I think she's ready.
Shipshape.

19:13.679 --> 19:17.848
Hey, guys! I'm so psyched you
invited me to take the boat out!

19:17.900 --> 19:20.100
Well, Jeff, we realized
how selfish we'd been,

19:20.152 --> 19:22.269
and we wanted to share
the boat-guy lifestyle

19:22.321 --> 19:24.071
with someone who'd
appreciate it.

19:24.106 --> 19:27.107
Awesome. So, can I cast off?

19:27.159 --> 19:29.443
You mean drive it?
Yeah, sure, knock yourself out.

19:29.495 --> 19:31.195
Hey, dad.

19:31.247 --> 19:34.164
Whoa! Hayley, Hayley, we just
invited Jeff to go sailing.

19:34.200 --> 19:35.783
But it's our anniversary.

19:35.835 --> 19:37.334
Of what?
Being married.

19:37.370 --> 19:40.955
And what better way to celebrate
than a sunset sail?

19:41.007 --> 19:42.423
Eh, mind the lines.

19:45.094 --> 19:48.095
[ Adventurous music playing ]

19:54.520 --> 19:59.390
[ Seabirds calling ]

19:59.392 --> 20:00.941
So that's what sailing's
supposed to look like.

20:00.977 --> 20:02.226
Would've been cool if we'd done that.
Yeah.

20:02.278 --> 20:03.894
So, how long till
the boat sinks?

20:03.946 --> 20:05.813
Mm, as soon
as the painter's tape

20:05.865 --> 20:09.199
that's covering the big hole
in the bottom disintegrates.

20:09.235 --> 20:10.401
Well, let's go get 'em

20:10.453 --> 20:12.820
and collect
that sweet boat insurance.

20:12.872 --> 20:14.788
Boat insurance?
Who insures a boat?

20:14.824 --> 20:16.907
I thought the play was
life insurance.

20:16.909 --> 20:18.242
What?

20:18.244 --> 20:19.910
I took out a very aggressive
policy on Jeff.

20:19.912 --> 20:22.162
Damn it, Roger,
we can't let them drown!

20:22.214 --> 20:25.416
It's, uh, it's actually a pretty
important part of the plan.

20:25.468 --> 20:27.468
The -- the, uh, crux,
if you will.

20:27.503 --> 20:29.253
Ugh, forget it. They lived.

20:31.140 --> 20:34.091
[ Panting ] That was horrible!
The boat just sank!

20:34.093 --> 20:36.260
And the life jackets
didn't help at all!

20:36.312 --> 20:38.262
It's like they're filled
with sand.

20:38.314 --> 20:40.347
Roger!
It wasn't me!

20:40.399 --> 20:42.483
Wait a minute.
[ Click ]

20:45.488 --> 20:47.104
Cocaine!

20:47.156 --> 20:48.989
Stan, do you know what
this means?!

20:49.025 --> 20:50.441
I sure do.

20:50.493 --> 20:52.672
It means all three of you
are going to prison.

20:53.488 --> 20:54.580
Wait, what?

